OL,3,CWhistleblower reveals how health
OL,4,Cauthorities left him devastated
OL,6,FHe told UTV trust management was
OL,7,Fsupportive at the time, but once his
OL,8,Fconcerns were raised at a meeting with
OL,9,Fthe Public Health Agency in August
OL,10,F2022, he felt a shift in tone.
OL,12,F"It is certainly the worst meeting
OL,13,Fthat I have ever been in, in my life,"
OL,14,Fhe told UTV.
OL,16,FDr McKenna said senior management
OL,17,Faccepted his concerns and knew changes
OL,18,Fhad to be made, however he felt
OL,19,F"pretty devastated" when the meeting
OL,20,Fwas over.
